  {
    "client_msg_id": "92308a75-9915-4810-bac1-03d937f2b777",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "But I've since decided that Datalog isn't expressive enough. Its problem isn't the non-existence of hierarchical data though, it's the inability formally reason about program properties such as termination. (That is, unless you impose severe and/or complicated restrictions on which programs are considered \"safe\".)",
    "user": "UCGAK10LS",
    "ts": "1624435390.029100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
